G-Dot.vim
=========

Overview
--------

`g-dot` is a vim plugin that allows you to repeat the last normal mode
operation over a sequence of lines.

Usage
-----

`g-dot` creates the following mappings while all behave like Vim's built in
`.` command and repeat the last change:

- `g.` in normal mode
- `g.` in visual mode (including blockwise)
- `.` in visual mode (including blockwise)
